{{About|a type of chromosome|the ancestral discovery method using autosomal DNA|Genealogical DNA test#Geographic origin tests}}

An autosome is a chromosome that is not a sex chromosome – that is to say there are an equal number of copies of the chromosome in males and females. For example, in humans, there are twenty-two pairs of autosomes, and in addition there are X and Y chromosomes which are sex chromosomes. 

